<TITLE>Substitute jobs could open doors</TITLE>
<TEXT>
WESTERLY  Working as a substitute teacher would be ideal for Angel-Lena Smith, of Westerly, a certified paraprofessional who is studying part time for her teaching certificate. 
 
I would like to get into the district to have my name known  the ideal schedule would be about three days a week, she said. Its all about networking, so by the time Im finished with school to be a teacher, that way Id already be in the district. 
 
Smith, 30, was among a steady stream of applicants who attended the school districts Winter Open House at the Westerly High School cafeteria Saturday. The event served as a job fair for substitute positions as teachers, paraprofessionals, custodians, and bus drivers. 
   
